@unnumbered Foreword

The primary target for InklingReader is GNU/Linux because this is a platform
that is not supported by the official software provided by Wacom. The most 
important work, figuring out the format, has been done by Herbert Ellebruch.@*
@*
The code Herbert provided used Windows-specific functionality, so his software
is effectively Windows-only as well. The WPI parser and converters for 
InklingReader have been completely rewritten. Herbert's code has been used as a
reference for the WPI format.@*
@*
InklingReader is free software licensed under the GPL version 3 or any later 
version. You are very welcome to contribute to InklingReader. The project's 
home is @url{https://github.com/roelj/inklingreader}.

